+{"id":"bd-0cjqo","title":"P0: wcstok overreads tracked unterminated delimiter","description":"[CRITICAL] `frankenlibc_abi::wchar_abi::wcstok` bounds the token buffer through the runtime policy decision on `start`, but it scans the delimiter string with `scan_w_string(delim, None)` and therefore ignores `known_remaining(delim)`. A valid caller can pass a tracked delimiter buffer without a NUL terminator; the ABI code then performs an unbounded unsafe read past that allocation while building the delimiter set.\n\nEvidence:\n- `crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/wchar_abi.rs:1556-1563` accepts non-null `delim` and `save_ptr`.\n- `crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/wchar_abi.rs:1578-1584` makes the runtime decision using only `start` as the address and `known_remaining(start)` as the suspiciousness input.\n- `crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/wchar_abi.rs:1591-1593` calls `scan_w_string(delim, None)` unconditionally.\n- `crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/wchar_abi.rs:135-153` shows `scan_w_string(..., None)` loops until a NUL with raw pointer reads.\n- Recent coverage in `crates/frankenlibc-abi/tests/conformance_diff_wchar.rs:461-490` always builds `delim` via `wcstring`, so it never exercises an unterminated tracked delimiter.\n\nRepro test shape: allocate `delim = malloc(4).cast::<u32>()`, write one comma codepoint with no trailing NUL, then call `wcstok(input, delim, &mut save)` in hardened mode. Expected: reject safely or bound the delimiter scan to `known_remaining(delim)`. Actual today: unbounded `scan_w_string(delim, None)` can read past the tracked allocation.\n\nFix direction: compute a delimiter bound from `known_remaining(delim as usize).map(bytes_to_wchars)`, pass it to `scan_w_string`, and treat `(len, false)` as an adverse safe failure instead of constructing an unterminated delimiter slice.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-29T03:35:12.286186635Z","created_by":"cod_2_reviewer","updated_at":"2026-04-29T03:35:12.286186635Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
